    "# Credit Card Fraud Detection — Machine Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "# Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This project builds machine learning models to detect fraudulent credit card transactions using insights derived from prior exploratory data analysis (EDA).\n",
    "\n",
    "The objective is to:\n",
    "- build predictive models\n",
    "- handle severe class imbalance\n",
    "- evaluate fraud detection performance\n",
    "- compare multiple algorithms\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Models Used\n",
    "\n",
    "- Logistic Regression (baseline)\n",
    "- Random Forest (ensemble model)\n",
    "- XGBoost (advanced boosting model)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Key Challenge\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud detection is a **highly imbalanced classification problem**, where:\n",
    "- Fraud cases are extremely rare\n",
    "- Accuracy is misleading\n",
    "- Recall and Precision are critical\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strategy\n",
    "\n",
    "- Use **SMOTE** to balance the dataset\n",
    "- Compare multiple models\n",
    "- Evaluate using:\n",
    "  - Precision\n",
    "  - Recall\n",
    "  - F1-score\n",
    "  - ROC-AUC"
   ]
